'''''Gremiphyca''''' is a lobed, non-mineralized [[alga]] with a pseudoparenchymatous [[thallus]], dating to the [[Ediacaran]] period.<ref name="Xiao2004">{{Cite journal | last1 = Xiao | first1 = S. | last2 = Knoll | first2 = A. H. | last3 = Yuan | first3 = X. | last4 = Pueschel | first4 = C. M. | title = Phosphatized multicellular algae in the Neoproterozoic Doushantuo Formation, China, and the early evolution of florideophyte red algae | journal = American Journal of Botany | volume = 91 | issue = 2 | pages = 214–227 | year = 2004 | pmid = 21653378 | doi = 10.3732/ajb.91.2.214}}</ref> The genus was reinvestigated by Xiao et al. and was interpreted to be a stem-group florideophyte.<ref name="Xiao2004"/>

