{{unref|date=February 2015}} {{Infobox Book | name = It's Not Luck | title_orig = | translator = | image = Its-not-luck.jpg | image_caption = Front Cover | author = [[Eliyahu M. Goldratt]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = [[English language|English]] | series = | subject = | genre = | publisher = [[North River Press (publisher)|North River Press]] | release_date = 1994 | english_release_date = | media_type = [[Softcover]] | pages = 283 | isbn = 0-88427-115-3 | oclc= 31443609 | preceded_by = [[The Goal]] | followed_by = [[Critical Chain (novel)|Critical Chain]] and [[Necessary But Not Sufficient (novel)|Necessary But Not Sufficient]] }}
'''''It's Not Luck''''' (1994) is a business [[novel]] and a sequel to ''[[The Goal (novel)|The Goal]]''. The plot continues to follow the advancement of the main character, Alex Rogo, through the corporate ranks of large [[manufacturer]], UniCo.
Author Dr. [[Eliyahu M. Goldratt]] continues to teach the reader his thinking processes through the eyes of Alex Rogo as he learns from his mentor, Jonah. In this book, the primary subjects are the resolution of conflict through the [[Evaporating Cloud|evaporating clouds method]] and the identification of root causes through the effect-cause-effect method.
In this book the main character, Alex, conducts the reader through the essence of some TOC tools and applications, like the [[Thinking processes (Theory of Constraints)|Thinking Processes]] and the TOC solutions for Marketing, Distribution and how to compose the Strategy of a company.
[[Category:Business books]] [[Category:1994 novels]] [[Category:Israeli novels]] [[Category:Theory of constraints]] [[Category:Sequel novels]]
